Asturian

[edit]

Etymology

[edit]

From asesín +‎ -ar.

Verb

[edit]

asesinar (first-person singular indicative present asesino, past participle asesináu)

  1. to assassinate

Spanish

[edit]

Etymology

[edit]

From asesino (“murderer”) +‎ -ar.

Pronunciation

[edit]
  • IPA(key): /asesiˈnaɾ/ [a.se.siˈnaɾ]
  • Rhymes: -aɾ
  • Syllabification: a‧se‧si‧nar

Verb

[edit]

asesinar (first-person singular present asesino, first-person singular preterite asesiné, past participle asesinado)

  1. (transitive) to murder
    Synonym: victimar
    Hypernym: matar
